rature fully accessible to Hispanists, folklorists, and all students of comparative literature and Judaic culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aLadino poetry. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / European / Eastern (see also Russian & Former Soviet Union).2bisacsh1 aArmistead, Samuel G., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSilverman, Joseph H., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSljivic-Simsic, Biljana08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn eBook Package Archive 1898-1999 (pre Pub)z97831104425260 cprintz978151280019740uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/978151280020340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781512800203423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781512800203.jpg  a978-3-11-044252-6  Penn eBook Package Archive 1898-1999c1898d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK